10, 1945 – Tigers 9, Cubs 3: Another radio broadcast here, from “Prince” Hal Newhouser's complete game as the Tigers won a deciding Game 7 at Wrigley Field – the Cubs’ last World Series appearance until 2016.
The “Curse of the Billy Goat” began after Game 4 in the first series held after World War II.
Mickey Lolich jumps into the arms of catcher Bill Freehan after the Tigers won Game 7 of the 1968 World Series.
That sent the crowd at Comerica Park into a frenzied celebration, as the Tigers headed to their first World Series in 22 years.
Armando Galarraga’s perfect night was spoiled by a blown call from first-base umpire Jim Joyce in the ninth inning.